This paper deals with query optimization for SPARQL endpoints, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel technique for query processing using compressed bit-matrices, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with optimizing queries for nested OPTIONAL and BGP patterns, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
